1
00:01:47,971 --> 00:01:50,072
Mistress Frieren is looking tired.

2
00:01:52,052 --> 00:01:53,052
Oh?

3
00:01:59,214 --> 00:02:00,435
And now she's out cold.

4
00:02:01,075 --> 00:02:02,075
We can't stop.

5
00:02:02,155 --> 00:02:03,155
I can carry her.

6
00:02:03,396 --> 00:02:06,637
But Mr. Stark, your axe... Oh, yeah.

7
00:02:07,817 --> 00:02:08,817
My hands are free.

8
00:02:08,897 --> 00:02:09,534
I'll just hold her.

9
00:02:09,558 --> 00:02:10,818
Uh...

10
00:02:19,653 --> 00:02:20,994
No, I think I'd better do it.

11
00:02:21,734 --> 00:02:22,734
Why's that?

12
00:02:23,115 --> 00:02:24,115
No reason.

13
00:02:33,100 --> 00:02:34,100
The audacity.

14
00:02:34,540 --> 00:02:37,622
A measly ten copper coins
is all the king could part with.

15
00:02:38,257 --> 00:02:39,257
What a cheapskate.

16
00:02:39,778 --> 00:02:40,778
I'm not surprised.

17
00:02:41,199 --> 00:02:44,761
Many heroes have tried and failed to
defeat the Demon King over the years.

18
00:02:45,021 --> 00:02:46,522
You can't fund every adventurer.

19
00:02:47,083 --> 00:02:48,083
It's no problem.

20
00:02:48,344 --> 00:02:50,725
We'll earn money to cover
our expenses along the way.

21
00:02:50,965 --> 00:02:52,605
There's nothing wrong with that approach.

22
00:02:54,888 --> 00:02:56,169
It's part of the adventure.

23
00:02:56,869 --> 00:02:57,869
I suppose so.

24
00:02:58,370 --> 00:02:59,811
Hold on, your weapon.

25
00:03:00,131 --> 00:03:01,332
That's the hero's sword.

26
00:03:01,792 --> 00:03:02,813
No, it's a replica.

27
00:03:04,595 --> 00:03:07,597
I once rescued a merchant who
was attacked in my hometown.

28
00:03:07,858 --> 00:03:09,259
This sword was my reward.

29
00:03:09,879 --> 00:03:11,661
The man said I'd be a hero one day.

30
00:03:12,221 --> 00:03:13,542
Probably told every kid that.

31
00:03:14,223 --> 00:03:16,344
That's what made you
choose this path in life?

32
00:03:16,825 --> 00:03:17,825
Not quite.

33
00:03:17,946 --> 00:03:20,888
See, there was this annoying brat
named Heiter at the village orphanage.

34
00:03:21,388 --> 00:03:24,831
He kept telling me I'd only ever be a
fake hero because I wielded a fake sword.

35
00:03:25,392 --> 00:03:26,512
He was such a pain.

36
00:03:28,365 --> 00:03:31,428
I figured if I proved him
wrong, I'd have the last laugh.

37
00:03:32,209 --> 00:03:33,209
So here I am.

38
00:03:34,391 --> 00:03:39,577
One of these days, I'll hold the real hero's sword
in my hand and use it to defeat the Demon King.

39
00:03:41,959 --> 00:03:44,221
But that'll never happen
if we don't keep moving.

40
00:03:45,062 --> 00:03:49,687
If you're wondering about the brat, he grew up to
become a fake priest who stays lost in his cups.

41
00:03:50,368 --> 00:03:51,449
I'm a real priest.

42
00:04:12,324 --> 00:04:13,324
Just a dream.

43
00:04:14,145 --> 00:04:15,145
You're alive.

44
00:04:15,647 --> 00:04:17,104
I was afraid you'd never wake up.

45
00:04:17,128 --> 00:04:20,470
I feel as though I've been here before.

46
00:04:21,391 --> 00:04:22,671
Perhaps I'm still dreaming.

47
00:04:23,252 --> 00:04:24,493
If you were, it'd be warmer.

48
00:04:25,420 --> 00:04:27,302
I underestimated the mountain weather.

49
00:04:27,842 --> 00:04:29,083
We need to keep going north.

50
00:04:29,604 --> 00:04:31,245
The village we're heading to isn't far.

51
00:04:32,066 --> 00:04:33,066
Very well.

52
00:04:33,808 --> 00:04:36,370
Now that you're awake, do
you think you're able to walk?

53
00:04:38,212 --> 00:04:39,212
No.

54
00:04:39,413 --> 00:04:40,049
Are you sure?

55
00:04:40,073 --> 00:04:42,776
You smell nice.

56
00:04:44,758 --> 00:04:45,758
Great.

57
00:04:45,939 --> 00:04:48,141
You must be tired from
carrying her this whole time.

58
00:04:48,381 --> 00:04:49,042
You rest now.

59
00:04:49,382 --> 00:04:50,382
I'll take over.

60
00:05:00,925 --> 00:05:01,925
Perv.

61
00:05:05,326 --> 00:05:06,326
What did I do?

62
00:05:09,207 --> 00:05:13,068
For a moment I thought we'd freeze to
death, but the blizzard is settling down.

63
00:05:17,869 --> 00:05:20,710
Wow, so there really is a village
this deep into the mountains.

64
00:05:23,770 --> 00:05:26,171
We've been waiting for
your return, Miss Frieren.

65
00:05:28,023 --> 00:05:29,584
You're chief of this village now?

66
00:05:29,925 --> 00:05:30,925
You're a child.

67
00:05:31,166 --> 00:05:31,706
That's right.

68
00:05:32,086 --> 00:05:33,588
I come from a long line of chiefs.

69
00:05:33,948 --> 00:05:34,948
I'm the 49th.

70
00:05:36,330 --> 00:05:37,991
Welcome to the Village of the Sword.

71
00:05:40,433 --> 00:05:42,775
We spotted a smashed-up
house on our way in.

72
00:05:43,596 --> 00:05:46,118
You must mean that old
hunting cabin that got destroyed.

73
00:05:46,879 --> 00:05:48,436
The Lord of the Mountains is to blame.

74
00:05:48,460 --> 00:05:49,460
The who?

75
00:05:50,141 --> 00:05:51,843
I don't remember there being a lord.

76
00:05:52,803 --> 00:05:54,505
I can't believe I'm actually here.

77
00:05:55,265 --> 00:05:57,127
You know of this place, Mr. Stark?

78
00:05:58,185 --> 00:06:00,146
This village used to
protect the hero's sword.

79
00:06:01,546 --> 00:06:07,449
According to stories, the weapon was hidden in a
sanctuary somewhere close by, stuck inside a mighty stone.

80
00:06:08,769 --> 00:06:13,751
Throughout history, many heroes tried to pull the
sword from its rocky sheath, but none were successful.

81
00:06:14,811 --> 00:06:16,352
Until 80 years ago, that is.

82
00:06:19,413 --> 00:06:21,494
Let me think, how did
they explain it in the legend?

83
00:06:22,354 --> 00:06:24,676
There is but one person
who can claim this sword.

84
00:06:25,016 --> 00:06:28,959
The hero who will drive off the great
calamity that aims to destroy this world.

85
00:06:29,300 --> 00:06:30,300
Yeah, that's it.

86
00:06:30,421 --> 00:06:32,082
You're talking about Himmel, aren't you?

87
00:06:32,522 --> 00:06:33,763
He was able to take the sword?

88
00:06:34,284 --> 00:06:34,880
Exactly.

89
00:06:34,904 --> 00:06:36,946
The story is pretty famous.

90
00:06:37,026 --> 00:06:38,866
Are you positive you've
never heard it before?

91
00:06:39,188 --> 00:06:39,468
No.

92
00:06:40,048 --> 00:06:41,750
Master Heiter never mentioned it.

93
00:06:45,052 --> 00:06:46,052
Here we are.

94
00:06:48,240 --> 00:06:50,240
Finally warmth.

95
00:06:50,522 --> 00:06:53,043
I must admit, I'm thoroughly
disappointed in you.

96
00:06:53,683 --> 00:06:56,644
You were supposed to return
here after half a century had passed.

97
00:06:56,964 --> 00:06:59,945
I'm a mild-mannered person,
but even I'm pissed off you're late!

98
00:07:01,426 --> 00:07:02,426
How'd that sound?

99
00:07:02,526 --> 00:07:05,006
My grandmother said I should
tell you that when you showed up.

100
00:07:05,347 --> 00:07:08,884
I told her everything would be
fine if I waited a little longer instead.

101
00:07:08,908 --> 00:07:12,809
The villagers here have protected
the Hero's Sword for generations.

102
00:07:13,149 --> 00:07:15,250
They can easily defend
themselves from danger.

103
00:07:15,978 --> 00:07:20,520
We can hold our own if needs be, but you
still have a duty you promised to fulfill.

104
00:07:21,440 --> 00:07:22,681
What is she talking about?

105
00:07:23,341 --> 00:07:24,698
Monster extermination.

106
00:07:24,722 --> 00:07:27,883
The area around the village
attracts quite a few of them.

107
00:07:28,843 --> 00:07:32,425
The Lord of the Mountains has been
in especially unruly pain as of late.

108
00:07:34,625 --> 00:07:36,606
I'll get started first
thing tomorrow morning.

109
00:07:37,166 --> 00:07:39,166
Better to deal with this
sooner rather than later.

110
00:07:57,201 --> 00:07:59,862
Why are there so many
monsters roaming near the village?

111
00:08:00,443 --> 00:08:02,782
Surely you could have hired
some traveling adventurers

112
00:08:02,806 --> 00:08:05,145
to take them out before they
became a problem for you.

113
00:08:05,626 --> 00:08:07,727
I wish I could, but that's not an option.

114
00:08:08,627 --> 00:08:10,549
Of course, because Himmel is the hero.

115
00:08:12,050 --> 00:08:14,431
Whoa, there's even more of
them swarming down there.

116
00:08:16,052 --> 00:08:17,532
Looks like they want inside the cave.

117
00:08:37,788 --> 00:08:39,812
Hey, Frieren, why is the...

118
00:08:47,536 --> 00:08:51,788
That's the Lord.

119
00:08:52,412 --> 00:08:54,352
No wonder I didn't recognize your name.

120
00:08:54,892 --> 00:08:57,013
You only showed up in the last 80 years.

121
00:08:58,033 --> 00:09:00,254
Not nearly long enough to be a Lord.

122
00:09:02,434 --> 00:09:03,434
Get up, Stark.

123
00:09:03,474 --> 00:09:04,615
I know you're not dead yet.

124
00:09:11,639 --> 00:09:12,539
You're so mean!

125
00:09:12,663 --> 00:09:13,763
??? nicely.

126
00:09:20,118 --> 00:09:27,322
Excellent work.

127
00:09:30,423 --> 00:09:32,465
I have fulfilled my duty to this place.

128
00:09:37,827 --> 00:09:39,724
Frieren, I don't understand.

129
00:09:39,748 --> 00:09:43,230
That's the hero's sword in there.

130
00:09:45,471 --> 00:09:48,093
It's what draws so many
monsters to the mouth of this cave.

131
00:09:48,897 --> 00:09:51,826
A powerful barrier prevents
them from gaining entry, but

132
00:09:51,850 --> 00:09:54,779
they can't shake off the
impulse to destroy the weapon.

133
00:09:55,580 --> 00:09:57,400
They must be truly terrified of it.

134
00:09:58,441 --> 00:09:59,901
You know that isn't what I meant.

135
00:10:00,842 --> 00:10:01,842
Yes, I do.

136
00:10:06,384 --> 00:10:09,905
Himmel tried, but he couldn't
pull the sword from the stone.

137
00:10:11,946 --> 00:10:12,946
Another failure.

138
00:10:13,246 --> 00:10:14,907
We'll keep waiting for the real hero.

139
00:10:18,268 --> 00:10:19,268
Are you okay?

140
00:10:20,089 --> 00:10:22,569
I don't think there's anything
wrong with being a fake hero.

141
00:10:23,630 --> 00:10:27,291
I'll still defeat the Demon King
and bring peace to the world.

142
00:10:30,031 --> 00:10:34,253
And when I'm done, nobody's going to
be concerned about me being a fake or not.

143
00:10:37,934 --> 00:10:40,154
In the end, Himmel lived up to his promise.

144
00:10:40,575 --> 00:10:43,455
Even without the fabled sword,
he managed to save the world.

145
00:10:44,136 --> 00:10:45,256
He was a real hero.

146
00:10:46,170 --> 00:10:49,292
Why was the truth covered
up in favor of this story then?

147
00:10:49,652 --> 00:10:53,193
Probably because people wanted
Himmel to be some mythic warrior.

148
00:10:54,074 --> 00:10:56,235
It wouldn't do for him
to fail inside the cave.

149
00:10:56,695 --> 00:10:59,737
There's no place for
embarrassing stories in a hero's tale.

150
00:11:01,517 --> 00:11:06,240
When a new generation comes of age,
they romanticize the heroes of the past.

151
00:11:11,182 --> 00:11:15,184
The truth of who a person was
falls away, and they become an idea.

152
00:11:31,493 --> 00:11:34,854
I always believed you would bring
safety back to our village, Ms. Frieren.

153
00:11:35,254 --> 00:11:36,295
I'm grateful as hell.

154
00:11:37,355 --> 00:11:39,136
My grandmother said to tell you that, too.

155
00:11:39,776 --> 00:11:42,137
Sounds like your grandmother
had quite the mouth on her.

156
00:11:42,997 --> 00:11:44,878
Guess I'll see you in another 50 years.

157
00:11:48,059 --> 00:11:48,599
See you then!

158
00:11:49,019 --> 00:11:50,460
And don't be late next time!

159
00:11:59,698 --> 00:12:03,020
Once we drop our belongings off at
the inn, you're free to do what you want.

160
00:12:03,360 --> 00:12:05,281
It's been a while since
we were in a real town.

161
00:12:05,582 --> 00:12:06,582
This'll be nice.

162
00:12:07,723 --> 00:12:09,304
What'll you do with your afternoon?

163
00:12:10,184 --> 00:12:12,302
I'm sure there are plenty
of shops we could explore.

164
00:12:12,326 --> 00:12:13,687
Not interested, thanks.

165
00:12:13,987 --> 00:12:16,108
I'd rather stay inside
and read some grimoires.

166
00:12:16,548 --> 00:12:17,005
I see.

167
00:12:17,029 --> 00:12:19,010
I'll go on my own, then.

168
00:12:20,010 --> 00:12:21,010
Oh, that's right.

169
00:12:21,912 --> 00:12:23,653
Today is Stark's 18th birthday.

170
00:12:27,296 --> 00:12:30,053
Don't you think that's something you
could have mentioned to me a bit earlier?

171
00:12:30,077 --> 00:12:32,958
I don't have anything to
give him as a birthday present.

172
00:12:33,399 --> 00:12:35,319
Just buy something for
him while you're in town.

173
00:12:37,280 --> 00:12:39,621
But I don't know what kind
of gift he would even want.

174
00:12:41,682 --> 00:12:43,043
I wonder who's to blame for that.

175
00:12:43,683 --> 00:12:45,263
You are, Mistress Frieren.

176
00:12:47,484 --> 00:12:51,026
Based on the way you're acting, I
assume you have a present for him?

177
00:12:59,342 --> 00:13:00,503
He's going to love this.

178
00:13:06,007 --> 00:13:07,628
A potion that dissolves clothing.

179
00:13:09,289 --> 00:13:12,772
According to my master, this is
the type of gift men enjoy receiving.

180
00:13:13,232 --> 00:13:14,553
Stark will be overjoyed.

181
00:13:21,118 --> 00:13:21,398
What?

182
00:13:21,899 --> 00:13:23,160
Curious to know how it works?

183
00:13:27,644 --> 00:13:32,687
I remember when you purchased this because I told
you to return the vulgar concoction immediately.

184
00:13:32,711 --> 00:13:36,195
I can't believe how crass you are.

185
00:13:38,618 --> 00:13:39,618
What a waste.

186
00:13:39,659 --> 00:13:40,881
This was expensive.

187
00:13:42,904 --> 00:13:44,225
What am I going to give him now?

188
00:14:02,798 --> 00:14:03,879
I forgot about this.

189
00:14:06,800 --> 00:14:09,181
I'll try to figure out what
he'd be interested in myself.

190
00:14:10,001 --> 00:14:11,462
With any luck, he won't notice.

191
00:14:14,303 --> 00:14:16,964
Mr. Stark?

192
00:14:21,046 --> 00:14:22,447
He must have gone out already.

193
00:14:26,257 --> 00:14:28,159
A warrior with an axe on his back?

194
00:14:29,160 --> 00:14:31,662
Yes, that young man helped
me push my cart up here.

195
00:14:31,902 --> 00:14:34,184
I think he said he was
headed towards the plaza next.

196
00:14:36,746 --> 00:14:39,288
We were hanging out with
him, but he left a little while ago.

197
00:14:41,030 --> 00:14:44,268
It was so brave the way he raced up
that tree and helped us climb back down.

198
00:14:44,292 --> 00:14:47,856
That boy stopped my rampaging cow.

199
00:14:49,737 --> 00:14:51,799
He's helped so many people in town.

200
00:14:53,950 --> 00:14:55,830
How could Mistress Frieren be so vile?

201
00:14:56,091 --> 00:14:59,771
There's no way he would appreciate
that disgusting potion, right?

202
00:15:01,732 --> 00:15:05,273
There you are.

203
00:15:21,037 --> 00:15:25,001
Cloud looks like a lady with huge boobs.

204
00:15:25,621 --> 00:15:26,843
So he is a pervert.

205
00:15:27,663 --> 00:15:31,187
Oh, dang, that one's a big pile of poop.

206
00:15:33,329 --> 00:15:35,451
No, he's just incredibly immature.

207
00:15:35,571 --> 00:15:37,413
I'll have to tell Fern about these later.

208
00:15:38,033 --> 00:15:39,771
How does he expect me to respond?

209
00:15:44,777 --> 00:15:45,880
Mr. Stark.

210
00:15:47,950 --> 00:15:49,851
Hey Fern, you've got perfect timing.

211
00:15:50,191 --> 00:15:56,875
Take a look at those... On
second thought, never mind.

212
00:15:58,776 --> 00:16:02,377
Um, anyway... Would
you like to go for a walk?

213
00:16:02,998 --> 00:16:03,998
Sure.

214
00:16:06,059 --> 00:16:08,280
So, seems like you're kind of upset.

215
00:16:08,481 --> 00:16:09,481
What did I do wrong?

216
00:16:11,862 --> 00:16:13,383
How to approach the subject.

217
00:16:14,924 --> 00:16:16,745
Please tell me what to apologize for.

218
00:16:17,690 --> 00:16:20,152
No matter how sly I am,
he'll know something's up.

219
00:16:20,832 --> 00:16:21,993
I should just be forward.

220
00:16:24,134 --> 00:16:27,416
Mr. Stark, is there anything
you'd like me to purchase for you?

221
00:16:27,936 --> 00:16:28,936
Wait, what?

222
00:16:29,737 --> 00:16:31,718
Today's your birthday, is it not?

223
00:16:32,519 --> 00:16:33,720
Yeah, I guess it is.

224
00:16:34,300 --> 00:16:36,340
But what's that got to do
with you buying me stuff?

225
00:16:39,003 --> 00:16:40,003
Don't play dumb.

226
00:16:40,084 --> 00:16:41,364
I want to get you a present.

227
00:16:41,705 --> 00:16:41,965
What?

228
00:16:42,445 --> 00:16:43,445
Why would you do that?

229
00:16:44,726 --> 00:16:45,787
Just forget about it.

230
00:16:46,107 --> 00:16:47,128
You're insufferable.

231
00:16:48,598 --> 00:16:49,598
Wait.

232
00:16:50,078 --> 00:16:50,559
Come back.

233
00:16:51,019 --> 00:16:52,619
I wasn't joking with you, I swear.

234
00:16:53,640 --> 00:16:56,941
It's just no one's given me a birthday
present before, so it sounded weird.

235
00:17:01,702 --> 00:17:02,242
That's right.

236
00:17:02,362 --> 00:17:05,803
Not a single gift from my master or
my family back when they were still alive.

237
00:17:06,423 --> 00:17:08,383
I didn't know that was
something that people did.

238
00:17:09,304 --> 00:17:10,845
Not even one from your parents?

239
00:17:11,745 --> 00:17:13,686
So it wasn't a custom where you come from.

240
00:17:14,086 --> 00:17:15,086
No.

241
00:17:15,506 --> 00:17:18,167
They probably just didn't care
enough to bother getting me one.

242
00:17:19,870 --> 00:17:24,733
My village valued warriors, which meant
that they looked down upon the weak.

243
00:17:26,334 --> 00:17:28,095
You put on a pathetic display.

244
00:17:29,096 --> 00:17:30,557
Can't you be more like Stolz?

245
00:17:31,157 --> 00:17:35,520
Not only is he unharmed, he doesn't have
a speck of dirt or a drop of blood on him.

246
00:17:37,301 --> 00:17:41,744
That clean white cape is undeniable proof that
he's the strongest warrior among you fools.

247
00:17:42,865 --> 00:17:44,726
You are the pride of our village, Stolz.

248
00:17:45,186 --> 00:17:46,447
I do my best, father.

249
00:17:50,469 --> 00:17:52,070
Then, of course, there's your brother.

250
00:17:52,430 --> 00:17:53,770
Our family's great shame.

251
00:17:54,191 --> 00:17:59,853
Despite the intense training he does every day, he's
too much of a weakling to stand against a monster.

252
00:18:04,015 --> 00:18:05,015
A storm approaches.

253
00:18:05,516 --> 00:18:06,516
Let's go home.

254
00:18:06,936 --> 00:18:08,777
I'll stay and spar with my brother.

255
00:18:09,077 --> 00:18:11,138
Fine, but he's a waste of your time.

256
00:18:11,438 --> 00:18:13,439
Do try not to injure him too badly.

257
00:18:17,541 --> 00:18:18,541
Stark.

258
00:18:23,365 --> 00:18:24,165
Brother.

259
00:18:29,043 --> 00:18:30,043
Sorry.

260
00:18:30,765 --> 00:18:32,246
You have impressive focus.

261
00:18:34,008 --> 00:18:35,189
One day you'll be stronger.

262
00:18:36,030 --> 00:18:38,312
Here, let me show you
how to fix your stance.

263
00:18:42,536 --> 00:18:45,515
Well, actually, my brother was
different from the rest of them.

264
00:18:45,539 --> 00:18:46,840
But...

265
00:18:56,518 --> 00:19:01,422
When demons attacked my village, I abandoned
him, fled while he stayed and fought.

266
00:19:02,363 --> 00:19:05,486
Maybe I shouldn't be surprised my
family never celebrated my birthday.

267
00:19:06,266 --> 00:19:08,308
I was the failure, the coward.

268
00:19:11,391 --> 00:19:13,532
I'm sure Himmel wouldn't
have run away that night.

269
00:19:18,577 --> 00:19:22,080
Mr. Stark, let's go pick
out something nice for you.

270
00:19:24,584 --> 00:19:26,005
The past is irrelevant now.

271
00:19:26,665 --> 00:19:28,686
And the Stark I know is a true warrior.

272
00:19:29,526 --> 00:19:31,247
He's never run away from a fight.

273
00:19:32,547 --> 00:19:34,588
But I can't guarantee that I won't one day.

274
00:19:35,448 --> 00:19:36,849
There's no way we'd let you.

275
00:19:37,989 --> 00:19:38,989
That's easy to say.

276
00:19:39,250 --> 00:19:41,450
If you won't pick what you
want, I'll choose something.

277
00:19:44,712 --> 00:19:46,153
Fine, fine.

278
00:19:49,863 --> 00:19:50,863
Hmm.

279
00:19:51,364 --> 00:19:52,361
This one is my favorite.

280
00:19:52,385 --> 00:19:53,106
Too expensive.

281
00:19:53,346 --> 00:19:53,766
Try again.

282
00:19:54,267 --> 00:19:55,267
Right.

283
00:20:03,855 --> 00:20:04,615
Welcome back.

284
00:20:04,755 --> 00:20:05,755
You took your time.

285
00:20:06,257 --> 00:20:07,257
What's going on?

286
00:20:07,558 --> 00:20:10,580
Why did you make us such
ridiculously large hamburg steaks?

287
00:20:10,840 --> 00:20:12,121
How are they ridiculous?

288
00:20:12,402 --> 00:20:13,922
This is what you eat on your birthday.

289
00:20:15,253 --> 00:20:17,921
Like I said, my master wasn't
one to give presents, but

290
00:20:17,945 --> 00:20:20,635
he always cooked me a big
Hamburg steak on my birthday.

291
00:20:21,355 --> 00:20:22,416
You knew about this?

292
00:20:22,896 --> 00:20:23,896
Hey, Stark.

293
00:20:24,096 --> 00:20:25,717
Didn't Eisen explain this to you?

294
00:20:26,237 --> 00:20:27,237
Explain what?

295
00:20:28,278 --> 00:20:30,498
Warriors are so bad
when it comes to sharing.

296
00:20:30,779 --> 00:20:32,779
I'd say that's fairly rich coming from you.

297
00:20:33,239 --> 00:20:36,301
You do have a point, but I
relate because I'm the same way.

298
00:20:36,801 --> 00:20:37,801
We're foolish.

299
00:20:38,261 --> 00:20:41,262
People don't know how you truly
feel unless you tell them directly.

300
00:20:42,743 --> 00:20:43,743
You see,

301
00:20:46,188 --> 00:20:49,346
Come to think of it, you always
make comically large Hamburg steaks

302
00:20:49,370 --> 00:20:52,831
whenever it's one of our birthdays,
so there must be a meaning behind it.

303
00:20:53,412 --> 00:20:55,893
It's a long-held custom
in my part of the world.

304
00:20:56,453 --> 00:21:00,555
These oversized servings are a way
to honor warriors who put in hard work.

305
00:21:01,536 --> 00:21:04,077
You can think of this as a
birthday present from me.

306
00:21:05,117 --> 00:21:06,118
Only one problem.

307
00:21:06,378 --> 00:21:08,219
You're the only warrior here, Eisen.

308
00:21:08,599 --> 00:21:11,080
Every person who works hard is a warrior.

309
00:21:11,841 --> 00:21:12,841
Is that true?

310
00:21:13,161 --> 00:21:14,161
Who can say?

311
00:21:15,244 --> 00:21:17,726
These are for warriors
who are putting in hard work.

312
00:21:19,767 --> 00:21:21,024
What are you making, brother?

313
00:21:21,048 --> 00:21:22,349
Hamburg steak.

314
00:21:22,409 --> 00:21:24,710
It's your birthday, right?

315
00:21:25,771 --> 00:21:27,192
This can be our little secret.

316
00:21:34,937 --> 00:21:35,157
Go.

317
00:21:35,618 --> 00:21:36,618
Run, Stark.

318
00:21:39,080 --> 00:21:40,221
You have to survive.

319
00:22:09,860 --> 00:22:12,260
Eisen wrote down the
recipe for me a while back.

320
00:22:13,914 --> 00:22:14,914
How does it taste?

321
00:22:23,579 --> 00:22:24,579
It's good.

322
00:22:29,462 --> 00:22:32,600
Also, I was able to salvage a little of this.

323
00:22:32,624 --> 00:22:34,705
I won't hesitate to pour
that on your head again.

324
00:22:35,717 --> 00:22:37,117
Uh, what is that?

325
00:22:37,478 --> 00:22:37,778
Nothing.

326
00:22:38,018 --> 00:22:39,418
Forget she mentioned anything.

327
00:22:39,738 --> 00:22:41,499
It's a valuable potion.

328
00:22:41,999 --> 00:22:42,999
Ooh, what's it do?

329
00:22:43,399 --> 00:22:43,999
Pervert.

330
00:22:44,259 --> 00:22:44,459
What?

331
00:22:45,020 --> 00:22:45,520
How so?

332
00:22:45,780 --> 00:22:46,780
Disgusting.

333
00:22:46,940 --> 00:22:48,200
Seriously, what did I say?

